Master Answer:
The publicly funded (free) HPV9 vaccine program has criteria that differs for males and females. Some individuals up to 26 years of age are eligible for the HPV-9 vaccine for free.
Speak with a nurse at your local health unit to determine if you are eligible for the free vaccine.
